  "prompt": "How do I know if some one has read my direct message on instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can tell if someone has read your direct message (DM) by checking for the \"Seen\" indicator. Here\u2019s how it works:\n\n1. **Sent Messages**: When you send a DM, the message will show a small circle with a checkmark (\u2713) next to it. This means the message has been sent.\n\n2. **Delivered Messages**: Once the message has been delivered to the recipient\u2019s inbox, the checkmark will turn into a filled-in circle (\u2713\u2713).\n\n3. **Read Messages**: If the recipient has opened and read your message, the message will show a \"Seen\" label, usually in blue, below the message. This indicates that the recipient has viewed your message.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Disappearing Messages**: If you send a disappearing message (a photo or video that disappears after being viewed), you\u2019ll see \"Opened\" instead of \"Seen\" when the recipient views it.\n- **Message Requests**: If you message someone who doesn\u2019t follow you, your message will go into their message requests. They won\u2019t see it unless they open the request. In this case, you\u2019ll only see \"Sent\" and \"Delivered\" until they open and read the message.\n- **Privacy Settings**: If the recipient has turned off \"Read Receipts\" in their settings, you won\u2019t see the \"Seen\" label, even if they\u2019ve read your message.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure, the absence of a \"Seen\" label usually means the message hasn\u2019t been read yet.",
